      <h3 class='article'>
        <a name="yangshao"></a>
        Yangshao Culture
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=22342' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Yǎng​sháo ​Wén​huà', 'Yangshao Culture')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">仰韶文化</a>
      </h3>
      <p>
        The <span class='bookTitle'>Yangshao Culture</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=22342' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Yǎng​sháo ​Wén​huà', 'Yangshao Culture')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">仰韶文化</a> was a matriarchal Neolithic culture from the central Yellow 
        River basin that dates from about 5,000 to 3,000 BCE.
        They were a very prolific pottery producing people and we know them mostly through their distinctive 
        <span class='bookTitle'>painted pottery</span>, frequently including rose patterns.
        Yangshao was first discovered in 1921 in Mianchi County, Henan Province.
        Most decorative patterns are black and / or red.
        From their distinctive pottery the Yangshao culture has been identified with Gansu, Shaanxi, Henan at the center
        and also present in Hebei, Inner Mongolia, Shanxi, Qinghai, and Hubei. 
      </p>
      <a name="string"></a>
      <div class="picture">
        <a href='illustrations_use.php?mediumResolution=pot_string_pattern_banpo400.jpg'><img class='use' src='images/pot_string_pattern_banpo400.jpg' alt='painted pottery' title='painted pottery'/></a> 
        <div>
          <div class='picture_header'><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25480' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'cǎitáo', 'painted pottery')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">彩陶</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25659' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '弦紋 xiánwén', 'string pattern')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">弦纹</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=8454' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '壺 hú', 'pot')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">壶</a></div>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=22342' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Yǎng​sháo ​Wén​huà', 'Yangshao Culture')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">仰韶文化</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25482' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'bàn pō', 'Banpo')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">半坡</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=2460' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '類型 lèixíng', 'type')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">类型</a>（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=910' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '約 yuē', 'approximately')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">约</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=22414' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Gōng​yuán​ Qián', 'Before the Common Era (BCE)')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">公元前</a>4500〜<a href='/word_detail.php?id=681' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'qián', 'in front of / before')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">前</a>4000<a href='/word_detail.php?id=438' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'nián', 'year')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">年</a>）
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=1559' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Shànghǎi', 'Shanghai')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">上海</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3974' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '博物館 bówù​guǎn', 'Museum')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">博物馆</a>
          <div class='picture_header'>Painted Pottery Pot with a String Pattern</div>
          Banpo style from Yangshao Culture (4,800&mdash;3,600 BCE)
          Shanghai Museum
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>
        We call the kind of pottery made by <span class='bookTitle'>Yangshao Culture</span> people
        <span class='bookTitle'>painted pottery</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=25480' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'cǎitáo', 'painted pottery')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">彩陶</a>.
        The painted designs were applied before firing.
        The firing process fuses the painted design with the clay making it quite resistant to fading and degredation.
        This is one of the reasons that a large amount of <span class='bookTitle'>painted pottery</span> has survived.
        The designs were mostly painted with black or red paint and included geometric patterns, plants, and animals.
        The main pigment in the red paint is iron and the main pigments in the black paint are iron and manganese.
      </p>
      <div class="picture">
        <a href='illustrations_use.php?mediumResolution=pottery_banpo400.jpg'><img class='use' src='images/pottery_banpo400.jpg' alt='painted pottery' title='painted pottery'/></a> 
        <div>
          <div class='picture_header'><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25480' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'cǎitáo', 'painted pottery')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">彩陶</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=9619' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'píng', 'bottle / vase / pitcher')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">瓶</a></div>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=25481' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shuǐ qì', 'water vessel')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">水器</a>，
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=22342' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Yǎng​sháo ​Wén​huà', 'Yangshao Culture')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">仰韶文化</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25482' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'bàn pō', 'Banpo')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">半坡</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=2460' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '類型 lèixíng', 'type')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">类型</a>（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=910' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '約 yuē', 'approximately')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">约</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=22414' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Gōng​yuán​ Qián', 'Before the Common Era (BCE)')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">公元前</a>4500〜<a href='/word_detail.php?id=681' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'qián', 'in front of / before')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">前</a>4000<a href='/word_detail.php?id=438' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'nián', 'year')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">年</a>）<br/>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=2887' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shǒudū​', 'capital city')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">首都</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3974' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '博物館 bówù​guǎn', 'Museum')" 
